<h1 id="title">ember-clock</h1>

<h2>Description</h2>

<p>
  This is an Ember-cli addon that provides a clock service to Ember applications.
  The clock can be used to update time-sensitive properties..
</p>

<ul class="clock">
  <li>
    <div>
      {{clock.hour}}
    </div>
    Hours
  </li>
  <li>
    <div>
      {{clock.minute}}
    </div>
    Minutes
  </li>
  <li>
    <div>
      {{clock.second}}
    </div>
    Seconds
  </li>
</ul>

<h2>ClockService</h2>

<p>
  The clock service is injected into all controllers and components.
</p>

<p>
  To use the clock in a template or in computed properties, bind to the clock's
  <code>hour</code>, <code>minute</code>, or <code>second</code> properties.
</p>

<p>
  In templates:
</p>

<pre><code>&#123;&#123;clock.hour&#125;&#125;
&#123;&#123;clock.minute&#125;&#125;
&#123;&#123;clock.second&#125;&#125;</code></pre>

<p>
  In computed properties:
</p>

<pre><code>property: Ember.computed('clock.second', function () &#123;
  // this will update every second
&#125;)</code></pre>

<h2>Install</h2>

The package can be installed from <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/ember-clock" class="npm-link" target="_blank">npm</a>.

<div class="panel code">
  <pre><code>ember install ember-clock</code></pre>
</div>

